[2026-03-18T11:34:17.124Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01B9VZd3QggYW8RpXFkScchD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. Here's what was changed in `packages/orchestrator/src/dispatcher.ts`:\n\n**Problem:** When a worker WebSocket disconnected mid-execution (OOM, container eviction, etc.), the dispatcher marked the execution as permanently failed and never re-queued it — silently dropping the work.\n\n**Fix (3 changes):**\n\n1. **Added `request` and `disconnectRetries` fields to `ActiveExecution`** — stores the original `ExecRequest` alongside every in-flight execution so it's available for re-queuing.\n\n2. **Rewrote `worker-disconnected` handler** — instead of permanently failing, it now:\n   - Re-queues the execution to the front of the queue (up to `MAX_DISCONNECT_RETRIES = 2` times)\n   - Carries forward the retry count via a placeholder active entry so `dispatchToWorker` preserves it\n   - Updates DB status to `queued` with a descriptive error message during retries\n   - Only marks as permanently failed after retries are exhausted\n\n3. **Simplified `busy` handler** — now uses the stored `request` directly instead of fragile DB reconstruction, with the old DB fallback kept as a defensive backstop."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":294,"cache_read_input_tokens":52075,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":294},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b500da2d-9507-4008-8b1b-785ca760ac43","uuid":"c8de408c-7eee-42d4-ad61-527ce770d80d"}
